    </tr><tr>
        <td align = "justify">
            PathoPlant&reg; is a database on plant-pathogen interactions and components of signal
            transduction pathways related to plant pathogenesis. PathoPlant&reg; also harbors gene
            expression data from <i>Arabidopsis thaliana</i> microarray experiments to enable
            searching for specific genes regulated upon certain stimuli like pathogen infection, elicitor
            treatment, or abiotic stress. Validation of short DNA sequences as <i>cis</i>-elements
	    responsive to different stimuli can also be performed in PathoPlant&reg;.
        </td>
    </tr><tr>
        <td>
                                
